---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Rat Poison vs. Fertility Management | Cloakd"
  description="Rat poison kills what's there. A new colony moves in within six weeks. Here's what poison alone doesn't address — and why the 90-day program produces a different result."
  path="/vs/rat-poison"
>

  <!-- ─────────────────────────────────────── HERO ── -->
  <section class="pt-20 pb-24 px-6 max-w-6xl mx-auto">
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <p class="text-[#c96a3a] text-sm font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase mb-6">
        Rat Poison vs. Fertility Management
      </p>
      <h1 class="text-5xl sm:text-6xl lg:text-7xl font-bold text-[#1c1814] leading-[1.08] tracking-tight mb-8">
        Poison kills the rats that eat it.<br />
        It doesn't stop the ones that come next.
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-[#1c1814]/70 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl mb-10">
        Poison does its job. The problem is what happens four to six weeks
        after the colony clears. An empty territory in a food-rich urban
        block fills from the surrounding population — at full breeding
        rate — before your next scheduled treatment.
      </p>
      <a
        href="/get-started"
        class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-7 py-4 text-base font-semibold rounded bg-[#b85530] text-[#faf8f4] hover:bg-[#c96a3a] transition-colors"
      >
        Start the 90-day program
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ─────────────────────────────────────── WHERE POISON WORKS ── -->
  <section class="py-24 px-6 bg-[#f0ebe0]">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-start">
        <div>
          <p class="text-[#c96a3a] text-sm font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase mb-4">
            Where it works
          </p>
          <h2 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-[#1c1814] leading-tight mb-6">
            It kills what's there. That part works.
          </h2>
          <p class="text-lg text-[#1c1814]/65 leading-relaxed mb-6">
            Rodent poison placed along travel paths and near entry points
            will kill the rats that eat it. The colony that's currently
            active goes down. For light infestations or one-off incidents,
            it's often the right first tool.
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg text-[#1c1814]/65 leading-relaxed">
            The problem isn't what it does. The problem is what happens
            four to six weeks after it does it.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <p class="text-[#c96a3a] text-sm font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase mb-4">
            Where it falls short
          </p>
          <h2 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-[#1c1814] leading-tight mb-6">
            Killing the colony makes the territory available.
          </h2>
          <p class="text-lg text-[#1c1814]/65 leading-relaxed mb-6">
            Rats are territorial. When a colony is present, their scent
            markers keep other groups out. Remove that colony with poison
            and those marks fade within days. The food source didn't move.
            The building didn't move. Rats from the surrounding block
            detect the open territory and fill it within weeks.
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg text-[#1c1814]/65 leading-relaxed">
            The replacement colony comes in at full reproduction rate.
            You're back to baseline before the next scheduled visit.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ─────────────────────────────────────── OTHER ISSUES ── -->
  <section class="py-24 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-[#c96a3a] text-sm font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase mb-4">
        Other problems with rodent poison
      </p>
      <h2 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-[#1c1814] leading-tight mb-12 max-w-2xl">
        The cycle isn't the only issue.
      </h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        {[
          {
            title: 'Secondary kill risk',
            body: 'Hawks, owls, and foxes that eat poisoned rats absorb the toxicant. Stronger rodent poisons — the anticoagulant type — carry the highest secondary risk and have been under increasing EPA restrictions for consumer use.',
          },
          {
            title: 'NYC restrictions',
            body: 'In 2021, NYC banned commercial exterminators from using the strongest class of anticoagulant rodent poison. What was standard practice a few years ago is now restricted. The approved list changes.',
          },
          {
            title: 'It produces dead rats',
            body: 'Poison creates visible evidence — dead rodents in food storage areas, near prep surfaces, or where tenants can find them. For restaurants, that creates its own inspection and liability exposure even when the treatment is technically working.',
          },
        ].map(({ title, body }) => (
          <div class="bg-[#f0ebe0] rounded-xl p-6">
            <p class="text-base font-semibold text-[#1c1814] mb-3">{title}</p>
            <p class="text-base text-[#1c1814]/65 leading-relaxed">{body}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ─────────────────────────────────────── SIDE BY SIDE ── -->
  <section class="py-24 px-6 bg-[#f0ebe0]">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-[#c96a3a] text-sm font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase mb-4">
        How they compare
      </p>
      <h2 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-[#1c1814] leading-tight mb-16 max-w-2xl">
        Poison and fertility management solve different parts of the problem.
      </h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="bg-white border border-[#1c1814]/8 rounded-xl p-8">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-[#1c1814]/55 mb-6">Rat Poison</p>
          <div class="space-y-4">
            {[
              { label: 'Kills the current colony', yes: true },
              { label: 'Visible evidence of action', yes: true },
              { label: 'Stops the replacement colony from forming', yes: false },
              { label: 'Reduces reproduction rate over time', yes: false },
              { label: 'No secondary kill risk', yes: false },
              { label: 'Safe for continuous food-environment use', yes: false },
              { label: 'Produces 90-day declining trend documentation', yes: false },
            ].map(({ label, yes }) => (
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                <div class={`w-5 h-5 rounded-full flex-shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center ${yes ? 'bg-[#7aab7e]/15' : 'bg-[#1c1814]/8'}`}>
                  {yes
                    ? <svg width="10" height="8" viewBox="0 0 10 8" fill="none"><path d="M1 4L3.5 6.5L9 1" stroke="#5e9263" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
                    : <svg width="8" height="8" viewBox="0 0 8 8" fill="none"><path d="M1 1L7 7M7 1L1 7" stroke="#1c1814" stroke-opacity="0.3" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
                  }
                </div>
                <p class="text-base text-[#1c1814]/70">{label}</p>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-[#7aab7e]/25 rounded-xl p-8">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-[#7aab7e] mb-6">Fertility Management (Evolve)</p>
          <div class="space-y-4">
            {[
              { label: 'Kills the current colony', yes: false, note: 'Phase 1 handles this' },
              { label: 'Visible evidence of action', yes: false },
              { label: 'Stops the replacement colony from forming', yes: true },
              { label: 'Reduces reproduction rate over time', yes: true },
              { label: 'No secondary kill risk', yes: true },
              { label: 'Safe for continuous food-environment use', yes: true },
              { label: 'Produces 90-day declining trend documentation', yes: true },
            ].map(({ label, yes, note }) => (
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                <div class={`w-5 h-5 rounded-full flex-shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center ${yes ? 'bg-[#7aab7e]/15' : 'bg-[#1c1814]/8'}`}>
                  {yes
                    ? <svg width="10" height="8" viewBox="0 0 10 8" fill="none"><path d="M1 4L3.5 6.5L9 1" stroke="#5e9263" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
                    : <svg width="8" height="8" viewBox="0 0 8 8" fill="none"><path d="M1 1L7 7M7 1L1 7" stroke="#1c1814" stroke-opacity="0.3" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
                  }
                </div>
                <div>
                  <p class="text-base text-[#1c1814]/70">{label}</p>
                  {note && <p class="text-sm text-[#1c1814]/45">{note}</p>}
                </div>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-8 bg-[#e8e0d0] rounded-xl p-6 border border-[#1c1814]/5 max-w-2xl">
        <p class="text-lg text-[#1c1814]/70 leading-relaxed">
          The 90-day program uses both. Phase 1 clears the current colony
          with whatever treatment is already in place. Phase 2 adds Evolve
          on top to prevent the replacement from forming at the same rate.
          Together they produce a declining trend. Separately, neither does.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ─────────────────────────────────────── PROOF ── -->
  <section class="py-24 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-[#c96a3a] text-sm font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase mb-4">
        Field data
      </p>
      <h2 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-[#1c1814] leading-tight mb-12 max-w-2xl">
        What a combined program produces over 90 days.
      </h2>

      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-10">
        {[
          { value: '79%', label: 'reduction in rodent track presence', sub: 'Location A — 5-month urban field study, Aug 2025 to Jan 2026', color: '#7aab7e' },
          { value: '88%', label: 'drop in track density at the same site', sub: 'Tracks per monitoring plate declined even where rodents were still present', color: '#7aab7e' },
          { value: '90%', label: 'fertility reduction potential', sub: 'When Evolve runs alongside an active pest control program', color: '#c96a3a' },
        ].map(({ value, label, sub, color }) => (
          <div class="bg-[#f0ebe0] rounded-xl p-6">
            <p class="text-5xl font-bold mb-3" style={`color:${color}`}>{value}</p>
            <p class="text-base font-semibold text-[#1c1814] leading-snug mb-2">{label}</p>
            <p class="text-base text-[#1c1814]/60 leading-relaxed">{sub}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ─────────────────────────────────────── CTA ── -->
  <section class="py-24 px-6 bg-[#f0ebe0]">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <div class="max-w-2xl">
        <h2 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-[#1c1814] leading-tight mb-6">
          Keep the poison. Add the layer that stops the cycle.
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-[#1c1814]/65 leading-relaxed mb-8">
          The program works with whatever treatment is already running.
          Your vendor stays. We add the fertility layer on top.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4">
          <a
            href="/get-started"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-7 py-4 text-base font-semibold rounded bg-[#b85530] text-[#faf8f4] hover:bg-[#c96a3a] transition-colors"
          >
            Start the 90-day program
          </a>
          <a
            href="/how-it-works"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-7 py-4 text-base font-medium rounded border border-[#1c1814]/15 text-[#1c1814]/70 hover:text-[#1c1814] hover:border-[#1c1814]/25 transition-colors"
          >
            How it works
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Base>
